    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 3: \"Fz5 stimulates the formation of presynaptic sites\"\n- \"Axonal Fz5 expression induces a 78% and a 36% increase in the number of synapsin I and bassoon puncta, respectively (Fig. 3C,D). Thus, expression of Fz5 in axons induces presynaptic differentiation in a similar manner to the synaptogenic factor Wnt7a.\"\n\nFig.4: \"Fz5 promotes synapse formation by binding to Wnt7a\"\n- \"Therefore, Fz5CRD completely blocks the synaptogenic activity of Wnt7a, suggesting that Fz5 mediates Wnt7a function at synapses.\"\n- \"In hippocampal neurons, the Fz5 shRNA mixture significantly decreased the level of endogenous Fz5, whereas nc-shRNA had no effect (Fig. 5C).\"\n\nFig.5: \"Fz5 knockdown abolishes Wnt7a-induced synapse formation\". Experimental description: - \"Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) Sprague-Dawley rat embryos ...\"\n- \"Transfected neurons were exposed to recombinant Wnt7a (50 ng/ml, R&D Systems) for 16 hours\" --> human species ('Recombinant Human Wnt-7a Protein\")",
